<h3>Digital Metrics</h3>
<ol>
<li> CTA: Call to action</li>
<li> PPC: Pay-per-click</li>
<p> Also known as “paid search” marketing. PPC is online advertising where you bid on keywords used in searches.</p>
<li> SEM: Search Engine Marketing</li> 
<p> A combination of SEO and PPC</p>
</li>
<li>SEO: Search Engine Optimization</li> 
<p>The art and science of “optimising” webpages<p></li>
<li>SERP: Search engine results page.</li>
<li>CTR: Clickthrough Rate</li><p>Total number of clicks / the number of impressions.</p>
<p>CPC: cost per click. The business pays a fixed amount per ad click. Each time a consumer clicks an advertisement the business pays a predetermined cost.</p>
</ol>

